art of CA1 and the proximal subiculum will process non-spatial information.Although most track-tracing studies do not reveal whether a connection is excitatory or inhibitory, we suggest that some of the known connections between regions of the network are likely to be identified as inhibitory interneuron projections, based on their layer of origin. These long-range GABA (γ-aminobutyric acid)-ergic connections probably mediate interregional binding.Sources of detailed knowledge, such as that presented in this Review and the accompanying interactive diagram, will prevent the loss of valuable knowledge and hopefully inspire creative minds to come up with new solutions for outstanding problems in the field.},
